gov.ornl.keva.table

Class UnsortedBucket

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.ornl.keva.table.TableValue
      • gov.ornl.keva.table.TableBucket
        • gov.ornl.keva.table.UnsortedBucket
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable<TableValue>

    public class UnsortedBucket
extends TableBucket
    An unsorted bucket is a simple implementation of a bucket in which all table values are stored in a simple queue. That means that independent values are not sorted and that explicit branches are not supported.
    Author:
    James Horey
